        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): suppress announce fallback for resolved targets",
        "body": "## Summary\n- carry delivery target aliases from cron target resolution into the source delivery plan\n- compare message-tool sends against the canonical target plus aliases, covering Slack names, raw IDs, channel:<id>, and session-resolved targets\n- add regression coverage for the SZ-1136 case where announce fallback duplicated after a message tool send to #abel-channel\n\nFixes SZ-1136.\n\n## Root Cause\nCron announce fallback suppression only compared the final resolved delivery target against the message tool target. In Slack, target resolution can canonicalize a configured name such as `#abel-channel` into `channel:C0AHNV28LQJ`, while the message tool records the visible send as the original name. Because the pre-resolved aliases were not carried into the fallback matcher, the run looked unsatisfied and sent the announce fallback.\n\n## Tests\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.cron.config.ts src/cron/isolated-agent/run.message-tool-policy.test.ts` — 40 passed\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.infra.config.ts src/infra/outbound/source-delivery-plan.test.ts` — 11 passed\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/cron/isolated-agent/delivery-target.ts src/cron/isolated-agent/run.ts src/cron/isolated-agent/run.message-tool-policy.test.ts src/infra/outbound/source-delivery-plan.ts src/infra/outbound/source-delivery-plan.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Notes\n`pnpm tsgo:test:src` currently fails outside this patch in `src/plugin-sdk/approval-reaction-runtime.test.ts` and `src/plugin-sdk/approval-reaction-runtime.ts` around `ApprovalActionView` / approval payload typing.",
